{"attribution":"Federal Emergency Management Agency, Ready.gov, Hurricanes, Simplified Chinese; no FEMA, DHS, or U.S. Government endorsement or affiliation is implied.","cases":[{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-001","input":"飓风十分危险，可能因风暴潮、强风、离岸流和洪水造成重大破坏。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-001","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-002","input":"飓风可能发生在美国任何沿海地区，或大西洋、太平洋的任何领土上。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-002","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-003","input":"历史上，风暴潮是美国飓风灾害死亡的主要原因。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-003","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-004","input":"在西北太平洋部分地区，飓风被称为台风。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-004","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-005","input":"东太平洋飓风季：5月15日至11月30日。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-005","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-006","input":"大西洋飓风季：6月1日至11月30日。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-006","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-007","input":"中太平洋台风季：6月1日至11月30日。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-007","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-008","input":"了解您的飓风风险飓风不仅是沿海地区的问题。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-008","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-009","input":"了解降雨、强风、洪水甚至龙卷风如何在飓风或热带风暴登陆点内陆很远的地方发生。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-009","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-010","input":"制定应急计划确保家庭每个成员了解并掌握您的飓风应对计划。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-010","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-011","input":"如果您或家庭其他成员是残障人士，请评估紧急情况下是否需要额外帮助。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-011","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-012","input":"确保您的企业制定了业务连续性计划，以便在灾难发生时维持运营。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-012","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-013","input":"了解您的疏散区域如果您居住在疏散区域，可能需要因飓风迅速撤离。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-013","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-014","input":"熟悉疏散路线，与家人及宠物一起演练，并确定避难地点。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-014","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-015","input":"遵循当地应急管理人员的指示，他们会与州、地方、部落及领地机构和合作伙伴密切协作。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-015","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-016","input":"他们将根据社区面临的威胁提供最新建议，发布安全措施。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-016","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-017","input":"识别预警与警报请确保拥有多种接收警报的途径。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-017","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-018","input":"请下载 FEMA 应用程序，您可以最多就全国五个区域，接收来自国家气象局的实时天气和紧急警报。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-018","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-019","input":"订阅您所在地区的社区警报，了解无需注册即可接收的紧急警报系统（EAS）和无线紧急警报（WEA）。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-019","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-020","input":"审阅重要文件确保您的保险单和个人文件（如身份证件）是最新版。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-020","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-021","input":"制作副本并将其保存在安全、受密码保护的数字空间内。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-021","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-022","input":"加固房屋清理排水口和排水沟，将户外家具搬入室内，考虑安装防飓风百叶窗。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-022","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-023","input":"做好技术准备一旦预报飓风来袭，请保持手机电量充足，购买备用充电设备以供电子设备使用。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-023","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-024","input":"收集物资为家庭储备足够的物资。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-024","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-025","input":"将药品、消毒用品和宠物用品放入应急包或汽车后备箱中。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-025","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-026","input":"飓风过后，您可能数天甚至数周无法获取这些物资。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-026","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-027","input":"帮助您的邻居与邻居、老年人或可能需要额外帮助以制定飓风应对计划的人士沟通，了解您该如何为他人提供帮助。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-027","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-028","input":"及时了解事态注意紧急信息和警报。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-028","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-029","input":"若您居住在强制疏散区，且当地官员要求您撤离，请立即行动。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-029","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-030","input":"应对天气确定如何最好地保护自己免受强风和洪水的侵害。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-030","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-031","input":"在指定的风暴避难所或室内房间避风。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-031","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-032","input":"如果您被洪水困住，请前往建筑物的最高层。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-032","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-033","input":"不要爬进封闭的阁楼。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-033","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-034","input":"您可能会被上涨的洪水困住。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-034","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-035","input":"不要在洪水中行走、游泳或开车。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-035","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-036","input":"仅六英寸的快速流动的水就可以将您击倒，一英尺的流动水可以冲走您的车辆。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-036","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-037","input":"请关注当地官方发布的信息和特别指示。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-037","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-038","input":"清理时请务必小心谨慎。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-038","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-039","input":"清理霉菌或其他杂物时，请穿戴防护服并使用合适的面部防护罩或口罩。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-039","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-040","input":"患有哮喘、其他肺部疾病和/或免疫功能低下的人士，即使对霉菌不过敏，也不应进入室内有漏水或可见、可闻霉菌滋生的建筑物。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-040","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-041","input":"儿童不应参与灾后清理工作。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-041","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-042","input":"请穿戴防护服，与他人协同作业。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-042","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-043","input":"在潮湿场合或如果您站立在水中，切勿接触电气设备。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-043","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-044","input":"如果能确保安全，请关闭主断路器或熔断器盒的供电，以防止触电。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-044","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-045","input":"请勿涉入洪水，因为其中可能含有导致疾病的危险病原体。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-045","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-046","input":"洪水中还可能含有碎片、化学品、垃圾和野生动物。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-046","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-047","input":"地下或倒塌的电线可能使水带电。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-047","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-048","input":"请将电话留作紧急情况使用。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-048","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-049","input":"灾后电话系统通常会中断或占线。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-049","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-050","input":"请使用短信或社交媒体与亲友联系。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-050","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-051","input":"请拍摄照片，记录下任何财产损失。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-051","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-052","input":"请联系您的保险公司寻求帮助。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-052","split":"article"}},{"classification":{"domain":null,"risk":null,"status":"needs_input_only_review"},"id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1/sentence-053","input":"部分资源可能仅提供英文版本。","provenance":{"raw_url":"https://www.ready.gov/zh-hans/hurricanes","source_case_id":"sentence-053","split":"article"}}],"converter_output_used":false,"dataset":"blind-v2","id":"ready-gov-hurricanes-zh-hans-v1","input_only":true,"license":"U.S. Public Domain","modification_notice":"Extracted only complete Simplified Chinese paragraph and list-item sentences from the checksum-pinned Ready.gov main element, removed navigation, images, external resources, phone/URL instructions, page furniture, and exact duplicates, and added input-only provenance; no expected text or converter output was used.","purpose":"candidate_source_pilot","review_policy":"domain_and_risk_must_be_assigned_from_input_only","source_class":"public_domain","stats":{"by_split":{"article":53},"eligible_pending_review":53,"exclusions":{},"raw_cases":53},"upstream_revision":"Ready.gov Simplified Chinese Hurricanes; page last updated 2026-07-09; retrieved HTML SHA-256: b120d204b706d1c7eb716dbef206d42578fe8b0f283d8190120ce7dec4ad009e","version":1}
